<subSubSection id="9868838366A65710CE3A6FC56436FEB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F8952C7004C6C950CF3667A49B881922" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B801A1BB5D3455E5A2A27710F069620" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As 
<taxonomicName id="855728C32DFD9701D2E624B2B71DA227" authority="Pierce, 1908" authorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Pierce" baseAuthorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Eupathocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eupathocera erynnidis" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erynnidis">
<emphasis id="0591734F8760CA369A2E2F2C64A75ADD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Eupathocera erynnidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this species has an unclear phylogenetic position (
<bibRefCitation id="5B871AE46EE22F121B3BB598946836D0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" author="Benda, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="252 - 265" refId="B4" refString="Benda, D, Votypkova, K, Nakase, Y, Straka, J, 2021. Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time. Systematic Entomology 46: 252 - 265, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" title="Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" volume="46" year="2021">Benda et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). It is also provisionally included in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="37216F8CFF135B85A661BEF762DC1D8F" authority="Pierce, 1908" authorityName="Pierce" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Eupathocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eupathocera" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6F3732AF1D7A3171BF6224A8EB628215" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Eupathocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pierce, 1908, stat. res. based on morphological evidence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
